io.micronaut.mqtt.v5.annotation

Annotation Type MqttProperty


  • @Documented
 @Retention(value=RUNTIME)
 @Target(value={PARAMETER,TYPE,METHOD})
 @Repeatable(value=MqttProperties.class)
 @Bindable
public @interface MqttProperty
    Used for binding arguments to MqttProperties.
    Since:
    1.0.0
    Author:
    James Kleeh

    • Optional Element Summary

      Optional Elements 
      Modifier and Type Optional Element and Description
      java.lang.String name
      Never used if applied to a parameter.
      java.lang.String value
      If used as a bound parameter, this is the property name.

    • Element Detail

      • value

        public abstract java.lang.String value
        If used as a bound parameter, this is the property name. If used on a class level this is value and not the property name.
        Returns:
        The name of the property, otherwise it is inferred from the name()
        Default:
        ""

      • name

        public abstract java.lang.String name
        Never used if applied to a parameter. Supplies the property name if used on a class or method. If the name is not one of the supported property names, the name and value will be populated via a UserProperty.
        Returns:
        The name of property
        See Also:
        for a list of names
        Default:
        ""
